<TITLE> Indonesia LSI exit poll puts Yudhoyono at 59.6 pct </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JAKARTA, Wed Jul 8, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Indonesian President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono is leading in the election with 59.6 percent of the vote, an exit poll issued by the Indonesian Survey Institute (LSI) showed on Wednesday. The exit poll is in line with indications in most opinion polls conducted ahead of the vote which had given Yudhoyono a clear lead. If accurate, it would also mean Yudhoyono would win in only one round. Yudhoyono is being challenged by Vice President Yusuf Kalla and former president Megawati Sukarnoputri, who had 11.0 percent and 19.3 percent, respectively, the exit poll showed. LSI said 10.1 percent of respondents declined to give an answer. The survey was based on 85 percent of the responses tallied so far from exit polls taken at 2,100 polling stations. LSI said the poll has a margin of error of plus or minus 2.8 percentage points. Quick count results, which in the past have proved highly reliable, are due in the next few hours. If no single candidate wins more than 50 percent of the vote, or 20 percent of the vote in 17 provinces, there will be a run-off between two candidates on Septemb
